caption: From the first moment  you come to this place  team give you an agreeable feeling. Very friendly crew, it is a happy restaurant to go out with buddies or with your date. tasty  food, specialist  chef, competitive  pay and nice  service. Warmly recommended.

My lady and I went here for a date night. I have never had Turkish food before and we thought it would be interesting to try out. The atmosphere was nice a cozy. The place was dimly lit, but we could still see everything inside. They normally have belly dancers there, but we just saw videos on the TV of past dancers. Duting the pqndemic, that's understandable.  The service was pretty good as each person came to our table in enough frequency to ensure we were taken care of. If there was an issue we only needed to address it once.  The food was also delicious and their ginerella tea...OMG! I wish I could make it on my own. The price of the food isn't much off Cheesecake, Olive Garden and the like, but I believe the service and food was more worth it here compared to the 2 chains restaurants and recommend giving them a try  Side Note...If you look the company up, they have a Baltimore and Columbia location.  The Baltimore location is under construction and only the Columbia location is open.

I can not stop dreaming everyday Cazbar food. I start to come here every week now, sometimes even 2-3 times.usually, I order lamb tree ways. I would recommend to everyone, who loves lamb. It is so delicious and fresh. I order also their most yummy and beautiful served  cocktail grand Istanbul. Thanks Manager Erdal for his smily face always. About server Salome- I can talk non stop about her. She is just amazing person. Such a lovely, warm, nice and productive person who works such a hard, I have never seen. You can see her honest and friendly smile even under her Mask. I think this is one of the main reason I come this often to talk to her as she speaks 4-5 languages as me and we always make so much fun. Thanks guys a lot to be around Columbia  to make lots of people’s life so happy even this Pandemic boring time. Wish you lots of more success in your business. 🤎
I travel from Towson to Columbia for their shrimp kabab. Great food, great services, Bartender/Server Salome is one of kind!!

I ordered muhamra, a walnut and red pepper dip served cold, and it had a round sweetness. The gluten free bread was a large, round, sliced like a pizza, lightly raised bread with Italian style seasonings (or at least that's what my western tongue can discern). It is so hard to find gluten free bread this good!

We love hanging out. Yesterday we arrived in this superb restaurant which friends recommended to us. We spent a beautiful evening there with very good meal and a well-trained team and a distinguished  chef. We put this place in our list  and we shall definitely go again very soon.  Highly recommended.
Lamb was really good.
turkish food... so great.
One of my fav spots for tasty Turkish food. I had a cousin come into town and she asked me to go back here.

Where have you been all of my life Cazbar? Friend and I recently dined here. From starter plates to a mixed grill entre, everything was magnificent and spiced on perfectly. Lovely service. It's not everyday you find Turkish cuisine in Baltimore to be this authentic. Can't wait to come back!

My friend took us for a surprise treat for our anniversary on Thursday. Lo and behold, i was captivated by the  elegance and ambiance of the place. Very spacious and well kept. The manager/ receptionist was very welcoming. We were met by our server Salome, she is  very attentive and entertaining. To top it off, the food was superb, cooked and served to perfection. Portions are huge and really worth every penny. Will definitely visit the place again.

Had a great experience at Cazbar in Columbia! Great food! I had the grilled Salmon, rice and salad. Salmon and rice were amaaazing! I also had the Baklava Cheesecake which was yummy, but SUPER rich (I recommend sharing it with someone else). Service was also fantastic! Merve, our server, was attentive and accurate and had a wonderful, positive energy :) Great environment as well with the Turkish music in the background. Very fun!

Turkish food... quality stuff. You will not be disappointed in the menu and service. I will be bringing family next time. This place has a great feel to it. Mood here reminds me of Colorado Springs area.
Big portions, good food, amazing environment! Friendly staff.
Excellent spot for turkish food. I love it here. The service was very welcoming and observant.

If you want to discover the tastes of your hometown or a new taste.  You are right in place.  A small suggestion, I recommend you to have an appetizer and drink raki with it.  In addition, all employees are very warm and sincere, especially Merve and Sallome. Thanks.

Just left Cazbar and it was the best Turkish restaurant that I’ve ever been. My sister is getting married next week and we decided to come here for dinner. Our waiter, Batu, played music for us, we danced after our meal, we laughed and overall an amazing time. Food was phenomenal as well. We were a group of 11 girls and felt like queens, service was just so amazing. Thank you Batu!
Wonderful atmosphere and food.

caption: Absolutely delicious food.  Slow service was the only reason it's not 5 stars.
My preferred place for turkish food. Visited near twelve, it was not full. Looking forward to a return trip. This place has a great atmosphere. I see why this place has so many good reviews.
Turkish food... my favorite treat. A preferred evening place. Looking forward to a return visit.
I very much enjoyed the food and service, fantastic area  to my home. The employees are always very friendly. Will visit here again.
Nice and beautiful waitress, great kebab and ayran
Turkish food, yeah, very delicious. Nice place to relax, people watch, eat good, etc.  The service was friendly and observant.
THIS FOOD IS AMAZING! WOW. Great service and great food.  I stop here everytime I know I'll pass by lol.
I love the food here, especially the kebabs, the portions are huge and the delivery is always fast!
turkish food... my favorite treat. Had a friend come into town and she asked me to take her here again. The place has a cool atmosphere.

The ambiance, food and location are second to none. This restaurant is spacious and luxurious. Everything is cooked to perfection. Most of all, you are greeted warmly and made to feel special by the friendly staff. The hostess greets me by name after only meeting me once. Salome is the most attentive server, with the sweetest spirit, who anticipates your every need. Cazbar makes my heart smile.

I went to Cazbar Columbia restaurant with my friends. O My god, it was incredibly amazing adventure. We ordered sultans platter entree and we never had food like that. Such a nice combination of tastes. We got also bottle of Turkish wine for half prize, and special cocktail ice bombom ice (maybe I wrote wrong name, but it was really taste made by lion milk) 🤩🤩 server Salome (❣️) was so sweet and beautiful. The way how she was paying attention to us was so kind and warm. She suggest us all of that food and drinks, it was really correct decision. I would really recommend this place to everybody. Their interior itself means to travel to Turkey and taste real food.👏👏
turkish food at this place - super tasty. entered near ten, it was not crowded. service treated us so kindly. the bill was reasonable.
The food was fantastic and the service was amazinggg!
Ordered take out. Was made on time; large portions for the price (was at least two meals); tasted great. Beautiful restaurant as well.
Good food. Good service
We love this place! Food is always delicious, service is great, and we love the belly dancers, too!
Fantastic and yummy food, I liked the vibes this spot has, and the staff members were friendly. I will definitely come back again.
I love this place. Great food and kind staff to support it.

Delicious food, portions a little small, messed up the order which was take-out so we didn't realize until we got home - but might be worth double checking your order. Nice authentic menu options too.

I like this place! They give high quality dishes, their menu is large, The chef in that spot is very trained, I enjoy a lot tasting all their dishes. Highly recommend the Gluten Free crab cakes. All Gluten Free pates are marked with a red flag stating they are gluten free. Not issues eating here. Highly recommend!!!

I ordered gyro plate and falafel. Gyro was real meat not ground beef. It was so delicious. And bread was fresh and delicious.

This restaurant is certainly great. Great environment, impeccable service, beautiful décor, delicious authentic food, and great portion sizes for a very reasonable price. I visited this place with some friends who have never had Turkish food, the fact that their menus were digital truly helped my friends make their selection. I tried their grilled shrimp kebaps and lentil soup on their lunch menu. It was delicious and enjoyed every bite. Check them out. They're  unquestionably worth the visit.

The food was delicious, and well presented.   The decor was warm and cozy. The service was mediocre. The space is small, and it was full, but didn't feel crowded.  I ordered a couple classic cocktails, which were too sweet for my taste, but thought maybe a Turkish twist?  At one point the music turned up and a a beautiful bellydancer  came out of nowhere!  Dancing through the restaurant and interacting with the pateons.  Definitely unexpected, but charming and memorable.

This place was a wonderful mix of ambiance and flavor. The food is to die for. The mixed platter for two was a feast, with traditional Turkish meat preparations, onion infused rice, with a suite of Mediterranean and Near-Eastern appetizers, heavy on the eggplant. It served not only two, but we took half of it home, and we were full. The music was modern Turkish pop, the drinks were a wonderful fusion of Turkish and cocktail standards.

The food was excellent. The atmosphere clean and elegant. Parking not too far. The service was subpar i.e. our drinks were empty. The tables were too small for the platter meal as things were falling off and hanging off. Website indicated belly dancing started at 9 when it was 9:30. Website overall is not good and had the place not been recommended I wouldn't have gone due to the Website.
A late valentines dinner with a sweetie and we had amazing service and stellar food.  Highly recommend going here.
Authentic Turkish food, great atmosphere, and exceptionally friendly staff.
Loved this place!!!
Delicious food in a sophisticated setting with friendly servers and good menu choices. I went with my son for his 18th birthday and he loved it.
Food was awesome.  I had grilled Salmon, salad and rice. Just enough to satisfy your tummy.  😊

I don't know about dinner but lunch is great. The freshest of bread. All the sandwiches are good. And you get a full plate of food - salad and fries. The pumpkin soup is a delight (rich and earthy). TV at lunch shows intriguing Turkish programs. Staff are dutiful. Prices fair.

This is my second time coming here and both times I had an incredible experience. I recommend coming on Friday and Saturday when you get to see a belly dancer perform. Theres just something about a great dinner and show. The food was seasoned to perfection I can’t find a fault with a single item on my plate( I had the lamb pirzole and chicken pirzole). The waitress Merv did a phenomenal job if recommending the Turkish sangria hands down in my top five of best sangrias in Baltimore. If you get the chance to definitely walk through the door and enjoy.

One of the best Turkish restaurants I've tried across many US cities. Very fresh and tasty mezes as well as amazing lamb kebaps.  Love that they serve Raki and Turkish wines and also have a good selection for Turkish desserts including my favorite kunefe!

This is one of my son's favorite places to eat in Baltimore.  The food is great as is the service.  And they are now high tech. The menu is a tablet with descriptions and photos.   The Turkish beer is one of my favorites- the only way they could improve on that is to have it on tap.  The closeness of the tables is my only complaint but that is reminiscent of being in Istanbul (for any who have been to Turkey).  Therefore the noise level is difficult for more mature people with subpar hearing.  But even with this negative I still rate them a 5 star based on the positives I mentioned above.  If you like Turkish food or want to experience authentic Turkish cuisine them you must try the Cazbar. I truly believe that you will be happy you did.

Absolutely incredible food. The lamb three ways (particularly the chops) and the starter dips (especially the babaganoush) are absolutely to die for. Our server, cannot remember her name, was a sweetheart.

I used to come here quite frequently until they raised their prices and cut their portions. I stopped by there today ordered my usual to go, my soup was $6.00 and measured 1/2 cup. If you go to other restaurants and you pay maybe 3.00 3.50. This place is gouging its customers.

Turkish food was very delicious and had the middle eastern authenticity. Baklava at the end was super tasty, don't miss it! They have ample drinks options as there is a bar section as well. Lighting and music was relaxing. Overall very nice dining experience!

Sam was by far a 5 star host. Great atmosphere and authentic food.

Great authentic Turkish food and such a nice atmosphere. Lovely and friendly staff, and very efficient service. Loved the menu system - easy to read and a great new experience. All in all overall a very good place to eat. Be prepared to eat lots though! I recommend the Adana Iskender.

Wow! This place was just what we needed on a chilly Baltimore night! The dining room was warm and inviting. All of the meats in the Mixed Grill were delicious, I would order a whole meal of any of them. We also ordered the trio of mezzas: baba ganoush, a garlicky yogurt and pickled beets with yogurt - all fantastic! The bread was soft and they brought more when we ran out. For dessert we had a fancy turkish coffee, kind of like a latte I guess and I took the baklava assortment to go. But the baklava was my favorite part! Chocolate baklava (choklava??) is amazing and so were all the other kinds. Best of all, they are all made exclusively with pistachios.  My only moment of "huh" was they were listed as being open until 11 and at 9:30 we were the only ones in the restaurant. At 9:30 they brought out strong bleach cleaner and started mopping the floor, leaving the bucket in the middle of the dining room. The smell was overwhelming and off putting. Which may have been intentional. When we tried to order coffee and dessert at 10 we were told the kitchen was closing so I guess they just operate as a bar until 11?
Great costumer service from Sam. It was my gf birthday and he made it amazing. Thanks Sam and I will see you again.

Try the Forbidden Sour and basically anything on the menu of this authentic Turkish Restaurant. Loved the ambiance, service and staff. Prompt, attentive and tasty. Recommend next time in downtown Baltimore.

Amazing Turkish cuisine in small setting. They had belly dancing as it was late Saturday night when we went. Little bit of wait due to we were 2 couples and a lot tables for larger groups were taken. This is great date night spot. The portions are nice for the pricing. The menus were all digital with great photos of the food.
A lot of interesting dishes to try and share! Generous portions on higher priced items.
Relaxed, classy atmosphere with fantastic Turkish cuisine, particularly a wide selection of Meze (small plates, similar to Tapas), and responsive, professional staff.

Menu looked great, unfortunately we'll never know if the food's any good because the service is atrocious. It was quiet when we arrived, three tables besides ourselves. While there appeared to be two servers - the man who sat us and the woman serving our section - the male appeared to be more interested in wiping off empty tables. The female server spent fifteen minutes trying to sort out a table next to us that couldn't figure out how to split a bill three ways. No one asked us for drinks or even acknowledged our presence beyond seating us. We had ample time to choose our wine and food,l from the menu, but after twenty minutes we were so frustrated by the poor service we decided to leave. Their loss. We both worked in the service industry and tip extremely well.

Love this place. Kofti sandwich is the best and their fries are delicious. It seems their menu changes everyday but the food is always good no matter what you try. Staff is always prompt and courteous! Definitely recommend. Overall 9/10!

This place is surely one of the best restaurants in the region. Every time I come to this place I am so pleased. They always keep their very high  standard service and the highest level of food  they offer. You are always happy with this place. Warmly  recommended.

This is the place to have. Good time, with amazing food and great performing belly dancing. I couldn't wish for a better 40th birthday celebration.

INCREDIBLE!  We had the platter for two. Included Meza (like appetizer dips) and several different types of meat and roasted vegetables. Cooked perfectly! So flavorful. The Baklava had to be the best that I have ever tasted, made with pistachios.  The sangria was pretty good too.

My wife and I loved eating here when in Baltimore. The atmosphere is cozy, the servers are knowledgeable and friendly, and the food is just so spectacular!  The bread they give you is always homemade, soft, and incredibly delicious. Order the trio of dips and you'll be in heaven. My favorite was the beet one, but the babaganoush and hummus were equally superb.  I may never eat a regular pizza again because the pides here are better in every way. Thin crust, deep dish, bah. Pides are the best because they incorporate a soft, thin crust with the flavors, spices, and toppings of Turkish cuisine.  The kebaps are also excellent and tender, full of meaty flavor.  I guess I've never had true Turkish food before, but this is a great introduction. Definitely worth a visit!

End with a Turkish coffee to feel even better after a good meal.Some of the best middle eastern food I have had in a long time! The service was impeccable. The waiters were friendly, courteous and eager to help. We are there on a Sunday night and the place was very busy, so reservations might be a good idea. Because it was so busy it was also a little loud. But that was a small price to pay for the wonderful food. And talking about price, my wife and I both had a main dish and a desert. I had a Turkish coffee and she had a glass of wine. The total was about $80 including a 20% tip.This place is a fun place to check out. The service is amazing and professional. The wait staff lined up looking for opportunities to take a plate or fill a glass without being too intrusive. I cannot speak highly enough of the staff. The food was pretty good but the price was way to high for the quality. You should expect to spend $15-$20 dollars per entree that probably should be prices at $7-$15 dollars for the size and quality.

Went here on a whim to try Turkish food, was not dissapointed. Restaurant itself is lovely with great Mediterranean ambiance. I had a Rose Martini (they made it with vodka for me because I don't like gin). I also had the lamb moussaka which was large, filling dish with eggplant, lamb, potato, tomato sauce and cheese. Similar to lassagna, but done with Turkish flavors. My husband had the mixed grill, which is a large plate with lots of different grilled meats. They had a variety of different seasonings and dipping sauce.  For dessert we split an order of baklava cheesecake, which had a nice balance of sweetness from the baklava and tartness from the cheesecake. Service was quick and friendly. I can absolutely see why this place is so highly rated, the accolades are well deserved!
Great food and entertainment as always. This place never disappoints.
